jpg|thumb|250px|Postcard published by Edmond Fortier showing the mosque in 1905-1906]] The Djinguereber Mosque () in Timbuktu, Mali is a famous learning center of Mali built in 1327, and cited as Djingareyber or Djingarey Ber in various languages. An ensemble of fifteen mannequins in the hall showcase fourteen traditional costumes of women from the Regions of Mali with the fifteenth showcasing the outfit of a modern Mali woman. The exhibit showcases the contribution of Malian women and seeks to correct the prevailing stereotypes about women.
